It keeps saying business was closed at 12:53 and couldnt be delivered. The address is a school address and it was open today at 12:53. I dont understand what is going on. I had parents order 300 dollars in books and we cant even get them delivered. Doesnt make me want to send out flyers again.
what school is opened on Saturday!!  Deliever during the school day.

Only received 4 books out of my 24 book
Order? With no explanation why.
Why are you trying to deliver to a school on Saturday?

The delivery was attempted on Saturday 10/7 and was supposed to be delivered on next business day. I have checked the tracking daily, with no changes in the status of the package. I called Scholastic and they said it was being held at USPS. I went there today to see if by chance my order was there. Sure enough, it was being held at the post office.
I tried to contact you to add my 10 books for my $200 purchase but no one has reached out to me. I tried to do it before the books shipped. So disappointed.
You keep wanting to deliver the books on Saturday :/ then kids not getting their book orders for over 2 weeks!!!!!

Ease of parent ordering. (I used to have to do a lot more to calculate totals to place an order.) Setting up the emails was the most time consuming part, but now that its done it should be pretty easy.
Books are a bit expensive, but I found what I was looking for and they were delivered in a timely manner.
Thank you for all you do for teachers, educators, parents and families!
I like that there is only one flyer for each grade.  It makes it easier to order.  I do miss the multicultural and diverse flyers that Scholastic use to have.
Thank you it was a day early the family was happy too
You keep wanting to deliver the books on Saturday :/ then kids not getting their book orders for over 2 weeks!!!!!
I tried to contact you to add my 10 books for my $200 purchase but no one has reached out to me. I tried to do it before the books shipped. So disappointed.

I am so dissapointed by the how much Scholastics changed their ordering system. I work at a title 1 school where I also have a lot of newcomers. Their only access to books is through scholastics. Most that come have no credit cards, or bank accounts. THe only way they would get books was by paying me cash and then I would place the order and pay with a card. The new system is difficult, creates more work for teachers and there is a lack of consideration for  those of lower socio-economics. I have taught for close to 30 years and was a regular customer of Scholastics.  I am now reconsidering if I want to continue ordering book.
I think parents dont all like on line shopping.  The number of parents participating is very low.  Im discouraged by this change.
One of my books is missing!!

I was supposed to get my books box today but I received an email saying that it was delivered today to some business and that it was closed. What business? My granddaughters teacher said that the books would arrived at the school. I dont know who to contact to straighten things out.
My orders are not arriving to the correct address! Still missing my last order!
The order was correct and all of the books were in excellent condition.

My order was placed weeks ago.  I have not seen a single update letting me know why it is taking so long.  This email has an order date over four years ago, which makes no sense.  Now, it looks like I am not even receiving the whole order in one shipment. I never have book orders placed or arrive during book fair, as I feel it takes away from the school wide ever, and now our school book fair starts tomorrow.
This was a fast way to fix the problem of a missing book from my order
I still have not received my package.

Was very upset to not see the dollar books when submitting my order as a teacher for a low income district. My students look forward to new books and now I can not provide them with as many as I could before.
The changes that Scholastic has made to the book club offered through the schools have been a huge step backward for our students. I am very dissatisfied.

I don't like the automatic submission feature. I don't get to use my points and it submits before I want it to. I give my families a week to submit their order so that I can then add my teacher order. This feature is beyond frustrating and makes me not want to use scholastic book club anymore. I've been using this site and ordering books for families and my students for 12 years. I am very close to never using this again.

As a teacher, I used to buy my kids a book for Christmas. It is insanely expensive to do that now and I can no longer even find the 10 book pack. Unfortunately, it looks like  I'm completely done buying for my students and that makes me really sad.
Can't find the schedule for ordering and do not like that I can't choose my own order due date.

It seemed like affordable books were lacking.  Please consider adding a few less expensive choices so all families can have books in their homes.  I always appreciated the $1 or $2 books that used to be offered each month.  Thanks!

I feel like we should not have to request catalogs. They should just come monthly like they did before. Students like to have them in their hand and circle the items they want. They get so excited when they are on paper. Not expecting digital flyers all the time. Plus our school district doesn't like the printing of these flyers. It's a cost to the district.
I put I want to order is out of stock.
It was great.  I didn't find everything I was looking for, but I still found some great books!

this redesign is disappointing.  Not being able to enter my own due dates, and the smaller number of available titles coupled with the much more expensive prices has kept me from sending this info to families sooner this year.  Many of my student's families have very tight budgets, and historically Scholastic has enabled them to order quality books at very reasonable prices.  Now prices are comparable to Barnes and Noble, but with lesser quality book construction and many fewer titles.  The dollar books and reasonably priced value packs enable me to use points for birthday books as well as holiday gifts for my 50+ preschool students.  This year I won't be able to do both.  I can't afford to pay cash for 50 books at these prices.  I'm afraid class participation in orders will be much lower this year.

I love Scholastic Books and have since I have been teaching, which is over 30 years!

I got no rewards from orders my students placed, which is the point of ordering from scholastic, that the classroom gains from orders placed.  When I contacted customer service, I was told that I messed up my submission (which I didn't), and they couldn't do anything for me without an additional phone call, which my order auto-submitted before I could make. I used to use scholastic every month a few years ago (I was a teacher for six years).  I was not a classroom teacher for a couple of years, and now returning, I'm incredibly disappointed.
I was hoping for some Science of Reading resources.
I am really excited about some of the changes!
Taking away the ability for families to place an order and send back to the school has proven to be a hardship for our families.  Many of them will not order online.

The navigation of the flyers is complicated. When you click details about a book from a flyer, you cant go back to the flyer without starting over. I also find the new layout of the winter flyer very difficult to view with the prices in different pages, especially when browsing online.

Parents ordered in September and we still don't have the books because I didn't realize you set the dates.  I am extremely dissatisfied with the new system and I most likely will be doing very little.
Every time I get on this site, I have trouble.

As a teacher, I have always used Scholastic Book Clubs to order books for my classroom and to promote the love of  reading with my students. I do that by introducing them to Scholastic Book Clubs. This year's format has CRIPPLED my way of doing things. Most of my parents are low socio-economic and do not use credit cards to pay for things. I collect money and order the books. Am I able to do it like this this year???? I doesn't look like it. I received the paper book club but it doesn't have an order form section???? This complicates things and I am trying to figure out how to do this using Scholastic Book Clubs. It is very difficult and thus far, sadly to say, not working for me,

I do not like how the flyers are this year as far as not having the order forms on the back for parents to fill out.  I read that it states it's easier, but this has not been the case for us so far.  I would much rather have the order forms on the flyers because not all parents use the online ordering so now they have to circle the books they want and still send in checks for payment. It gets a bit confusing..

Our UPS delivery driver has tried to deliver our book box twice after 4:00 pm.  There is no one in the church office or the preschool office this late.  We have missed our box twice.  Not happy.  Is there a way to specify a delivery time or to request the delivery person just leave the box? Thank you!

The changes are getting confusing. I am getting emails that orders were automatically submitted but I never placed the order. Also, how am I still getting points for submitting at different times throughout the month?
It seems the selection is not as big as it has been in years past.
The site is sometimes hard to move around. I wish it would open up to the flyers so you could look at the site as if you were looking at the flyer
SOMETIMES NAVIGATION OF THE SITE IS CONFUSING.

I have been saving my points for years. Year after year I have tried my best to submit orders and earn as many points as possible enough to get my so desperately needed laptop. Now I see that its ni longer available. I am so disappointed. It makes me so sad. I know things have changed but Im not enthusiastic about Scholastic anymore

I have had a very busy beginning to the year and wasn't sure if I was going to do the book orders this year. I asked my students and they said that they would like to have the flyers. I need to ask parents if they would like to have their emails placed on the computer for Scholastic before I proceed any further (I didn't realize that this was the new protocol). Quite frankly, I will encourage parents to purchase if you will go back to having literature that has both a well written and engaging story, as-well-as, artwork that is tastefully rendered (so often it is so crudely created that you would think that little children never deserve any loveliness or beauty in their life).  Please bring back some of the beautiful books of the past decades (I have been teaching from 1980. I was raised in a family of highly educated and artistically gifted parents/relatives.). I personally have many beautiful books from Scholastic, however during the past 10 or so years, Scholastic is a difficult and

This was a great site and a great way to get books in the hands of children. But the new changes are not easy. I have yet to have a book order this school year. I normally have one every month or so as a small school and class size I don't expect huge orders, but this has been nothing. Please return ordering to how it was.

This new system is not very user-friendly. I live on a Native American reservation, and for the first time in 7 years, I had no one place an order this month. When I tried to place a teacher order, I was given two different amounts that were going to be charged to my credit card: one included nearly $9 in shipping costs, and the other didn't seem to include shipping. So I canceled my order. I will not be sending Scholastic book order fliers home to my families this year. You can remove me from your mailing list if it's going to continue this way.   Michelle Becksvoort,  1st/2nd grades  Zuni Christian Mission School  Zuni, NM
I was looking for the Wolves of the Beyond series, hoping to order all six books, but Scholastic does not have them.

If you are going to make the rewards terrible - atleast drop the prices.  You seem to have increased the prices and made the rewards worse. Sad

I was looking for the Wolves of the Beyond series, hoping to order all six books, but Scholastic does not have them.

I have just entered my 20th year of teaching and have always been a HUGE fan of Scholastic Book Clubs. However, I must say that my opinion has changed this year. The prices are extremely high. Also,  I'm not sure why you went back to prices ending in .99 cents. Whole dollar amounts were much easier for my first graders to understand and save up their own money to buy books. Also, as a teacher, I purchase books for my entire class multiple times a year but won't be able to do that this year because the prices are just too high to buy 30 copies of something.  There also seem to be a lot more "toys" in the magazines this year, rather than books. We need our kids to be reading! They are already getting enough play time and I don't think the toys provide any educational value. Lastly, while I know that most people have internet access these days, the fact that parents are no longer able to send a check to the teacher and have the teacher order for them is just not equitable. I work at a tit

The changes made to Scholastic Book Clubs this year make it difficult for my families to have equal access to books.    First of all, the books seem more expensive than they have in the past. The prices are similar to what they would pay in the store and more than the prices at the used book store in our community.    Second, the removal of the order form from the flyer makes it difficult for many of my families to order. Some families don't have access to a computer for online ordering, while others are new to the country and do not have credit cards for online payment.     Thank you for your interest in making the experience better for teachers and the communities they serve.

I like your "old version" of  your book order magazine better.

I had today $15 out of my own pocket for taxes for my recent order. The students gave me cash for their order but did not include the taxes. Your clientele is predominantly teachers and families of students, and the teacher often takes the roll of communicating on behalf of families. When dealing with teachers we are TEACHING during the day and to participate in a chat and never get pulled away to a student is not always possible. I had to complete two chats and start over from scratch to get the problem resolved. The first one closed out of the chat without any warning because I had not responded for 7 minutes!!! The second one at least gave me a warning and thankfully the problem was resolved before they ended the chat. The first one though said they would handle it, then closed the chat, and had not handled the situation so I had to handle it AGAIN.  Overall, I am unhappy that teachers do not have a say whether to participate in the automated ordering and that even if there is an order in the cart it does not automatically go with the automated family order. I have students that cannot buy online, so they brought me cash and I placed the order for them. I have always handled my own family orders and placed them on the last day of each month. I was unaware of the automated order so the item in my cart was not placed with the auto order, and I am not going to pay shipping on this item when it should be free when included with the family orders. This new change makes sense in streamlining ordering however it is not equitable for all students/schools and there is not a work-around for teachers ordering on behalf of students. It either needs to automatically include the items in the teacher cart with the family orders or teachers need to be able to select this option or teachers need to be able to opt in/out of automatic orders.   I appreciate that the first person in the chat was willing to waive the shipping, but honestly, they were very impatient with their wait times to help. It is conference week, so I do not have time during the day until after 5:00 PM PST to deal with this other than during my lunch and it took so long to get the ball rolling that I had students coming in waiting for directions before I could finalize the support in the chat. I think based on the demographics of the clientele, representatives should not be held to strict time schedules for solving their issues and there should be a way for other representatives to access previous chats. Once I got the second representative, I had to begin the entire process and explanation all over again; again, while I am trying to teach and have students in class   In general, I am frustrated with these new changes and not very satisfied with how the chats are handled and timed out. Thank you for the work both reps did on waiving the shipping fee as a one-time courtesy.
